1
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:13,888
CAGE

2
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:40,957
Tomiyama-san's crazy...

3
00:01:09,277 --> 00:01:10,695
Huh?

4
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:12,864
That's weird.

5
00:01:12,947 --> 00:01:15,575
I was sure my punches landed...

6
00:01:15,658 --> 00:01:18,244
Your fists are light.

7
00:01:19,704 --> 00:01:20,663
Huh?

8
00:01:21,664 --> 00:01:23,291
Do you know why?

9
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:32,175
Because they don't shoulder anything.

10
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:37,013
I don't get you at all.

11
00:01:37,096 --> 00:01:40,683
I don't know what this whole
"light" thing you're babbling about is...

12
00:01:42,268 --> 00:01:45,313
but if I keep punching you
until you're down, it's all the same.

13
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:49,692
I'll hit you enough times so you'll know!

14
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:06,668
Like I said...

15
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:10,547
it ain't working on me!

16
00:02:26,437 --> 00:02:28,690
Sheesh...

17
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:31,901
That hurts...

18
00:02:33,736 --> 00:02:37,073
I'll become free, no matter what.

19
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:39,576
Don't get in my way!

20
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:45,999
What is this "free" thing
you keep going on about?

21
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:50,128
It means having fun!

22
00:02:52,046 --> 00:02:56,217
Then, what is "fun" to you?

23
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:03,641
To fight someone strong, like right now!

24
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:08,980
But you sure don't look like
you're having fun.

25
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:13,484
You don't know anything about yourself.

26
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:17,322
That's why you feel empty
and keep saying "what ifs."

27
00:03:17,947 --> 00:03:19,741
That must be hard.

28
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:22,368
I feel sorry for you.

29
00:03:23,786 --> 00:03:25,872
But even more than that...

30
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:31,336
I feel sorry for the team that
let someone like you be at the top.

31
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:35,757
Whatever the reason is,
you still became their leader.

32
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:37,884
Then...

33
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:41,971
don't let them make a face like that!

34
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:50,939
I'm really glad I came to Furin.

35
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:54,984
I'm glad that he's the top of our team.

36
00:04:01,991 --> 00:04:04,577
A face like... that?

37
00:04:07,163 --> 00:04:10,416
<i>No, this was from a long time ago...</i>

38
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,386
I don't get it.

39
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:24,722
I don't know. I don't get it.

40
00:04:26,557 --> 00:04:29,227
Shut up. Shut up.

41
00:04:29,769 --> 00:04:31,479
Shut up!

42
00:04:31,562 --> 00:04:33,606
I don't know. I don't get it.

43
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:35,483
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

44
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:48,246
Fine, whatever.

45
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:52,709
I don't need you anymore.

46
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:57,422
I don't need anything.

47
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:36,979
<i>When did the world become gray?</i>

48
00:06:38,272 --> 00:06:41,025
<i>It's dark... It's cold...</i>

49
00:06:41,776 --> 00:06:43,861
<i>No matter what I do,
I'm still unsatisfied.</i>

50
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:45,905
<i>I always feel so empty.</i>

51
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:46,864
<i>It's like...</i>

52
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:51,369
<i>my heart has turned into a barren desert.</i>

53
00:06:53,162 --> 00:06:55,248
<i>What is it that I'm missing?</i>

54
00:06:55,331 --> 00:06:57,125
<i>Why am I lacking?</i>

55
00:06:59,127 --> 00:07:00,628
<i>I don't know.</i>

56
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:03,756
<i>Ah, I don't care anymore.</i>

57
00:07:04,590 --> 00:07:06,551
<i>I'm sure it's helpless now.</i>

58
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:10,179
<i>No matter what I do, no matter what I get...</i>

59
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,973
<i>It'll just all be the same.</i>

60
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:15,017
<i>If so, I don't need it.</i>

61
00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:17,395
<i>I don't need anything.</i>

62
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:24,902
Cho... Choji...

63
00:07:43,171 --> 00:07:45,548
Hey, is he all right?

64
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:47,508
Why is he not fighting back?

65
00:07:48,176 --> 00:07:49,594
<i>Umemiya...</i>

66
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:51,220
What the hell are you doing?

67
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:54,223
You're the one boasting about
absolutely not going to lose!

68
00:07:54,307 --> 00:07:55,683
What's the meaning of this?

69
00:07:55,808 --> 00:07:57,435
He'll die...

70
00:07:58,769 --> 00:07:59,812
Hey.

71
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,397
Shut up and watch.

72
00:08:14,285 --> 00:08:15,995
Tomiyama.

73
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,289
Sorry.

74
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:21,751
I didn't mean to push you
over the edge like this.

75
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:26,547
I didn't realize you'd been driven
into a corner this much.

76
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:29,634
Shut up!

77
00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:32,220
But... if you keep spiraling in desperation...

78
00:08:32,303 --> 00:08:34,055
and end up destroying everything...

79
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:37,266
from here on out... you will never...

80
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:39,894
be free from that suffering.

81
00:08:39,977 --> 00:08:43,189
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

82
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:48,319
Tomiyama.

83
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:51,113
It's all right.

84
00:08:51,697 --> 00:08:54,242
The answer is inside of you.

85
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:59,163
I don't know what you're talking about!

86
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,668
Do you remember...

87
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:08,339
when our teams fought before?

88
00:09:09,131 --> 00:09:13,427
Turned out... it was all...
just a misunderstanding.

89
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:16,347
Retreat!

90
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:21,269
Man, you're stupidly strong!

91
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:23,646
You saved me again.

92
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:25,022
Yeah, same here!

93
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:27,650
Thanks. We'd be toast without you!

94
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:31,279
I'm glad to hear that!

95
00:09:32,113 --> 00:09:33,781
Ume-chan!

96
00:09:33,864 --> 00:09:35,658
That was super fun!

97
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:38,119
Let's do it again someday!

98
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:43,749
Back then, your fists were a lot heavier.

99
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,501
Heavier than today.

100
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:49,714
You were shining so dazzlingly back then.

101
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:51,882
Brighter than you are now.

102
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:55,928
What did you have around you back then?

103
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:59,015
What did you see with your eyes?

104
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:08,899
Stay away!

105
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:29,211
<i>It's warm...</i>

106
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:32,632
Remember, Tomiyama.

107
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:38,679
What you saw back then...

108
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:43,184
That's what you need,
and what's needed to be the top!

109
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,811
Thank you.

110
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:48,939
Remember what it's like!

111
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:50,941
Tomiyama!

112
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:56,906
<i>Huh?</i>

113
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,784
<i>What happened?</i>

114
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:02,453
<i>Why do you guys look
like you're having so much fun?</i>

115
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,627
<i>How nice.</i>

116
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:11,962
<i>Let me join in, too.</i>

117
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:32,066
{\an8}Hey, Tomiyama!

118
00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:37,196
What are you doing?

119
00:11:37,613 --> 00:11:40,157
The kitty looked like it wanted petting.

120
00:11:40,241 --> 00:11:42,326
You're so laid-back.

121
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,162
We're going into a fight
right now, you know?

122
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:48,874
If you wanna be the next general,
you gotta get your stuff together, man.

123
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:52,795
By the way...

124
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:55,297
who are we fighting this time?

125
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:56,507
Huh?

126
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:04,432
Man, you're definitely
gonna be a big shot one day!

127
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:06,392
Yeah, I can't wait.

128
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:07,726
It's in your hands.

129
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:09,520
Yeah! Just leave it all to me!

130
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:10,688
Let's go!

131
00:12:10,771 --> 00:12:13,232
-We're counting on you.
-Don't get beaten, okay?

132
00:12:13,774 --> 00:12:15,985
<i>Ah, this is so fun.</i>

133
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:18,195
<i>I wish this would continue forever.</i>

134
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:20,698
Hey, Kame-chan.

135
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:23,117
Huh?

136
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:25,494
Kame-chan?

137
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:28,539
Arima?

138
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:30,207
Numa-chan?

139
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:33,335
Where did everyone go?

140
00:12:57,985 --> 00:12:59,195
Kame-chan?

141
00:13:07,077 --> 00:13:09,205
<i>Huh? What's this?</i>

142
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,248
<i>Oh...</i>

143
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:12,958
<i>This is a dream, huh?</i>

144
00:13:14,668 --> 00:13:15,961
<i>But somehow...</i>

145
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:18,506
<i>it feels so nostalgic...</i>

146
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:29,099
Huh? Kame-chan?

147
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:33,479
Why are you making that face?

148
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:47,535
Oh...

149
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:49,119
So...

150
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:51,997
I lost to Ume-chan.

151
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:55,543
Kame-chan.

152
00:13:55,626 --> 00:13:59,505
I had a dream about a long time ago.

153
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,258
<i>Everyone was smiling.</i>

154
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:05,678
<i>I haven't had that much fun
in a really long time.</i>

155
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:09,181
And I think I get it now.

156
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:14,478
I had a lot of fun, too,
when everyone was smiling together.

157
00:14:15,437 --> 00:14:17,606
So, please...

158
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:18,566
smile.

159
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:26,615
Sorry, Choji.

160
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:31,745
I left you all alone.

161
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:38,377
<i>Not understanding
why you were suffering the whole time...</i>

162
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:41,380
<i>I distanced everyone from you.</i>

163
00:14:44,091 --> 00:14:46,552
I didn't want you to hurt
the rest of the team...

164
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:50,931
and make them hate you.

165
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:57,062
I couldn't let my ideal be broken.

166
00:14:58,063 --> 00:14:59,648
Ideal?

167
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:13,120
The ideal world where everyone loves you,
and I'm there, supporting you.

168
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:20,419
<i>That's why, on that day...</i>

169
00:15:20,961 --> 00:15:23,172
<i>although I knew what I did was wrong,</i>

170
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:24,757
<i>I looked away from you.</i>

171
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:28,302
But someone made me realize...

172
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:31,013
<i>No matter how strong my opponent is...</i>

173
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,932
<i>even if it's someone I owe my life to...</i>

174
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:36,644
<i>I won't look away or bend my will!</i>

175
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:39,188
As a member of Shishitoren...

176
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:46,570
I should've confronted you
for what I believed in.

177
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:50,240
I'm sorry I didn't talk to you...

178
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:54,411
I'm sorry I didn't look
for the answer with you.

179
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:56,872
I'm sorry I left you all alone.

180
00:15:57,665 --> 00:16:02,544
As a result, I took away
the thing you needed the most.

181
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,381
I'm sorry.

182
00:16:05,881 --> 00:16:08,092
I'm sorry, Choji.

183
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:12,346
Kame-chan.

184
00:16:12,846 --> 00:16:14,056
I...

185
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:20,062
honestly believed that being at the top
meant that I would have the most fun.

186
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,067
Let's go!

187
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:29,321
<i>It's like having my eyes on
a treasure chest on top of the mountain.</i>

188
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:31,073
<i>I was so thrilled.</i>

189
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:35,577
<i>I was sure that getting it meant
I would be freer than anyone else.</i>

190
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:39,748
<i>I was so excited imagining what
would happen once I opened the chest.</i>

191
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,726
<i>But when I finally got to it...</i>

192
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:02,229
<i>there was nothing.</i>

193
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:09,695
<i>I didn't feel anything at all.</i>

194
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:19,496
<i>I was scared.</i>

195
00:17:21,248 --> 00:17:23,333
<i>I felt like I was hollowed out.</i>

196
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:27,171
<i>I didn't know where I should go next.</i>

197
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:31,842
<i>No matter what I did, I felt nothing.</i>

198
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:34,595
<i>It all became meaningless.</i>

199
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:37,306
<i>I had to do something...</i>

200
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:40,267
<i>I struggled, wondering what wasn't right.</i>

201
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:42,770
<i>As I struggled, and kept on struggling...</i>

202
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,898
<i>I eventually couldn't see
anything anymore.</i>

203
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:49,610
<i>And I blamed it all on everyone else.</i>

204
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:54,948
<i>I told myself that I was not free and
having fun because the team was weak.</i>

205
00:17:55,491 --> 00:18:00,829
So I thought if everyone in the team
became strong, everyone would be free...

206
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:04,666
and then, finally,
I'll have the fun I was searching for.

207
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:08,462
You didn't take anything away, Kame-chan.

208
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:13,217
I was the one who said I didn't need it.

209
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:15,969
Right...

210
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:17,054
I...

211
00:18:17,721 --> 00:18:22,059
<i>had the most fun back when
everyone would laugh like idiots together.</i>

212
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:25,395
I was already free.

213
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:28,774
But I failed to realize that.

214
00:18:28,857 --> 00:18:30,067
Not only that...

215
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,695
<i>I destroyed it myself.</i>

216
00:18:39,034 --> 00:18:41,203
I'm so stupid, aren't I?

217
00:18:41,954 --> 00:18:46,083
If you weren't there for me,
I would've truly lost everything.

218
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:47,292
No.

219
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:51,296
Ume-chan told me...

220
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:54,842
to not let you make a face like that.

221
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:59,346
I just never saw it. Never tried to...

222
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:09,106
But you've probably looked like that
for a long time now.

223
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:17,948
I'm the one who made you
look like that, right?

224
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:23,120
But even still, you were the knot
that kept me tied to everyone else.

225
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:26,498
Thank you... for protecting me.

226
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:35,007
I'm sorry, Kame-chan.

227
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:38,177
You must've been hurt.

228
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:40,053
You must've suffered so much.

229
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:43,891
I'm sorry.

230
00:19:43,974 --> 00:19:45,017
Sorry.

231
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:47,311
I'm so sorry.

232
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:08,957
Thank you, Kame-chan.

233
00:20:09,499 --> 00:20:11,210
I'm okay now.

234
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:16,089
I gotta go and settle the score for good,
one last time.

235
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:25,515
Ume-chan.

236
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:34,733
I lost to you.

237
00:20:34,816 --> 00:20:36,485
Hey!

238
00:20:36,568 --> 00:20:37,611
Tomiyama...

239
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:40,614
So I'm quitting Shishitoren.

240
00:20:41,782 --> 00:20:44,493
Shishitoren is yours now.

241
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:49,206
Please take care of them.

242
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:59,424
Huh? I don't wanna!

243
00:21:01,718 --> 00:21:05,055
You were the only one betting your team,

244
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:07,474
but that was never my intention.

245
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:10,477
I'm not interested in making
my team any bigger, either.

246
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,854
All the hierarchy thing
is a pain in the ass!

247
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:14,898
But...

248
00:21:19,236 --> 00:21:20,362
Then...

249
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:23,073
how about we become friends instead?

250
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:27,035
So, you know, this fight today
is one of those...

251
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:29,329
like, socializing event?

252
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:32,749
So, hey! Thanks everyone for coming!

253
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,334
Did you all have fun?

254
00:21:35,043 --> 00:21:36,878
So what's happening?

255
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:38,797
I don't know.

256
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:47,931
You're always so funny, Ume-chan!

257
00:21:51,435 --> 00:21:54,229
All right! We're done for today!

258
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:56,523
Let's head on home!

259
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:35,455
{\an8}What is "fun" to you, Sakura-san?
Other than fighting.

260
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:36,790
